The paper discusses security risk management in the context of the Internet of Things (IoT), which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a game-theoretic model to capture the decision-making process of IoT users, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the cognitive network formations of players, which is a topic in social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the interdependence of decision-making and cognitive network formations, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a proximal-based iterative algorithm to compute the solution concept, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
